channel.title: Haven't been in the RSPS scene for a while, got a few questions?
channel.description: I haven't done anything with a RSPS for around three years. But I came back now and I've been browsing the forums. Like in the advertisement section, I saw like two posts for a 317 server and a bunch for 600+ servers. Have 317 servers lost their popularity since jagex released RS 07? And also, I've seen a lot of posts of people saying delta is a crap source. But can someone explain why? Because I've always used delta and I found it fairly good compared to PI which seems to be famous now.

item.title: Haven't been in the RSPS scene for a while, got a few questions?
item.dc:creator: @Elrick Elrick
item.description:
@Elrick wrote:

Jagex owns the most updated and full functioning 317, so it’s kind of pointless to make anything around that, assuming it doesn’t bring something new to the table.

Anything before EoC will be pretty popular, probably even moreso if it predates the horrendous armour update they did. Most players could stand pre EoC RS though.

Can’t help you on Delta and PI trends, as I haven’t actually ever looked at them.

Read full topic
